caption: Expensive but kind of expected just based on probably anybodys judgement. It's very nice and is a very lit up setting. It has an outdoor deck also for the warmer days & nights. The food isn't too expensive but there are a few items that are expensive. There are very expensive drinks as well which I was surprised with by the bill. I think a waiter should tell somebody the price before they actually pour the drink if it seems like they don't know what they're talking about. It's just professionalism. There is a big screen to watch games or whatever's on but overall it's a 5 star restaurant venue that has expensive liqours and professionally cooked food. If you have a taste for expensive liquor than this is a good place.

Upscale, beautiful decor, spectacular views, competently done food and drinks with a great spirits, wine, and beer selection, and on point servers. With the attached parking garage you don't even need to get out in the rain or snow. There are lots of chef-quality dishes on the menu, some being complete surprises. A case in point is the deceptively simple bruschetta appetizer, which is normally a boring dish with diced tomatoes. The Vue's version is the best I have ever had. They use sliced artisan baguette with melted mozzarella, sliced and roasted tomatoes with balsamic drizzle, all on a bed of baby greens. Delicious. One server said that dish is the reason she wanted to work at the restaurant in the first place. I think the one menu hiccup is the bread you can order. Surprisingly it's not artisan bread, so I believe it's below the standard of quality on the rest of the menu. I suggest having a generous portion of really good French or Italian bread with some great butter. This is what other fine restaurants do. Fortunately most all the other menu items are outstanding. All in all, it's one of the best Iowa City restaurants. I think you'll like it.

We got room service from them just last night. Everything was fresh and spiced beautifully. They were also thoughtful enough to add enough utensils and napkins, which you’d think would be a given, but lately seems to be a challenge for a lot of any type of takeout or delivery in our recent experiences.

Brought my girlfriend here for her birthday and our 6 years anniversary. The vibe is awesome, and the environment is pretty quiet. Definitely a nice dating spot. I understand the table arrangement/reservation might be a little tricky with the social-distancing in place, but well, it is still a little disappointing. However, later in the night as more customers are leaving, we requested to be moved to the patio area, and they DID move us, so at least we get to enjoy our dessert with a nice view!  As for the food, I ordered a medium-rare Filet Mignon and that is definitely the BEST Filet Mignon I've had before. 200% recommend it.

My boyfriend and I celebrated our 1 year anniversary here and we were pleased with the experience. The food was awesome and Zach W.'s service was great--he even brought us a dessert he had garnished and drawn with a heart on the plate! Very cute. Food I'd recommend: NY Strip Steak, Cheddar mash, Scallops, Polenta...everything we ordered. We'll be back :)
Aptly named, good cocktails. Come for the view, stay for it too

A little disappointing actually.  The view is terrific. The seating and decor is terrifically appointed and I have a lot of respect that they showed restraint for putting giant tv's everywhere. The place LOOKs, posh, stylish, high end. But a dining experience is a whole lot more than a joint that looks like they hired a solid interior decorator. That's why Leaf Kitchen is one of the best dining experiences in the area hands down.  The food is a little bit basic for the venue. It kind of looks like they just made some adjustments to the Black Stone or Stella's menu. Maybe it's the same people that own it? I like those establishments a LOT for upscale neighborhood restaurants. I rate those places as 4-5 star any day because what they are is what they propose themselves to be. Whereas the Vue could be so much more. The area has a lot of upscale eateries but very few that have executive chefs that stake their restaurant on an inspiring concept, or an inventive style like the top flight places like you see in NYC or Chicago. That is an gap to fill and Vue has the opportunity and venue to do it!  Last and perhaps most importantly, their waiters are real green horn novices. I mean we encountered 3-4 servers in our short visit there and none of them knew a significant amount about the menu, or the food, or their drink menu. Really disappointing. I also think uniformed waiters with name badges is an incredibly tacky way to staff a venue like this. Get at least a couple of great people with experience, give them some dress guidelines and let them make serving an experience with their own style, their own charm, and customers will appreciate the expertise and authenticity.  I hope the owner of this joint will read this and take my input to heart as a constructive critique. And I hope anyone who reads this will go and try for yourself. Maybe I'm being over critical, but I wanted this place to be more. I'll be back again a few times I'm sure. I'd love to revise my review.
Slick place with good service. However expect high prices and unimpressive food.
Nice place. Expensive but the views are nice. Some of their appliances were down the day we went so it shrunk a already small menu. The food was good.
They are close. Tune the lighting and some minor decor modifications and The Vue will be 'the top'. Service was excellent, my food order was delicious and took a stand on real flavor.
I wouldn't come here for the food but the drinks were delicious and the view was truly wonderful. Sit on the patio if you can!
Steak and eggs just do so but my wife’s broccoli wrapped in bacon was delicious. Service was attentive. Interesting views. But I somehow feel they could have done a better design with this place.

People told me they loved it, so I went expecting good things. I thought the food was mediocre at best to be honest.  Flatbread was just a giant chunk of melted fresh mozzarella and crust, pasta was kinda bland, and apps weren't too impressive either. I didn't even take my leftovers home. View and service were good though. I've seen gimmicky places like this pop up in big cities where you pay for location. Didn't think I'd see one show up in IC for a while, but here we are. I'll go back and give it another shot, but wasn't impressed overall with my first visit.
Nice vue, food okay
Great drinks but bad food.
Still need to get their online reservations figured out! So frustrating to think you have a reservation but no, they don't have it when you arrive.
Great view...great service ...great food... what more can you ask for??? And you can see old capital in the distance....

Overall you mainly go here for the view, they had decent wings and good drinks. I would avoid the flatbread, it was not to good. They need a new dough and sauce if I were to try it again. Honestly it reminded me of lunchables pizza...

Very much enjoyed the three visits I've made to Vue in the last couple of weeks, but I've found quality and serving size to vary, even when I've ordered the same menu item. The crab cakes I saw being served last night were 3x larger than ones I got a couple weeks ago. The margarita flat bread I had last night was bland and tasteless, but I really enjoyed the one I was served just days before. Service has been consistently excellent and I love the decor and view!
